I can understand Holland's Spidey being called a "murderer" because he was framed by Mysterio and JJ Jameson. Raimi's Spider-Man didn't even kill his villains. They all accidentally died at their own hands. Green Goblin: Glider. Doc Ock the building is falling apart, etc. Harry sacrifices, Venom loses the symbiote, Sandman I forget, but how do you murder sand? Did they put up the wrong one? And if you're opening Pandora's box to a Spiderverse, what about that 70s show Eddie Brock and Kirsten Dunst MJ? If this suit is in the trailer, they have to be in that universe. And then also in Holland's when Michael Keaton shows up.
